post_text: In a normal year, the month of May is a victory lap for seniors. They are celebrated by our community and school in a whole lot of different ways. This year is obviously not a normal one. So instead, we're using the month to show love to all of our seniors who have sacrificed so much at the end of their high school careers. We'll be posting Senior Spotlights throughout May to honor the Class of 2020.

We hope all will join us virtually!

post_text: Each day, we've been sharing Senior Spotlights for the Class of 2020. What you didn't know, is that in partnership with Wickshire Deer Park, these signs have also been printed and will be posted in the Wickshire Senior Living community. Signs will be hung throughout the next two weeks, and then given to the students to keep! Follow along on the Wickshire page to see which signs are posted! #SeniorsSupportingSeniors
shared_text:
Wickshire Deer Park
May 12 at 3:00 PM ·

With graduation fast approaching, we’ve teamed up with Deer Park Community City Schools to honor students as part of our Seniors Celebrating Seniors Program. During the next week and a half, we will highlight several students from Deer Park Jr/Sr High School’s class of 2020 and will hang signs in our front yard celebrating their achievements.

By bringing together the seniors in our community, both residents and students, we are helping support those who have been affected by COVID-19. We are so excited to share this collaboration, and we can’t wait to start highlighting the amazing seniors in our community! #SeniorsCelebratingSeniors #WickshireWay
www.wickshireseniorliving.com

Deer Park Community City Schools added 17 new photos.
March 6 at 11:27 AM ·

"Life is 10% what happens to us and 90% how we react to it." Charles Swindoll

Many students at Amity Elementary are learning about the Zones of Regulation which is a concept of self-regulation and emotional control. The students learn about 4 Zones of Regulation (Blue, Green, Yellow, and Red) where they can categorize feelings.

Blue Zone is when you are sick, tired or bored. Green Zone is when you are happy and ready to learn. Yellow Zone is when you are wiggly or frustrated. And Red zone is when you are angry, yelling or out of control.

Ms. Geselbracht had some volunteers act out the zones. Can you guess the Zone?

Deer Park Community City Schools added 23 new photos.
January 19 at 9:13 PM ·

Feature Grade: 4th Grade

The Amity Elementary Spelling Bee is something fourth-graders look forward to being able to participate in for the first time each year. The fourth-grade “classroom champions” were excited to be a part of this long-standing tradition. Fourth-grader, Fate Davenport, surprised and wowed us all by coming in second place out of all the candidates including fifth and sixth graders!

Students in fourth grade have been working with pattern blocks to learn more about angle types and measures.

Some of our fourth-grade students have been working on a Social Studies research project on different landforms. They will be making a model of their landforms with paper mache!

Deer Park Community City Schools added 34 new photos — in Deer Park, Ohio.
January 11 at 8:15 PM · Deer Park, OH ·

Feature Grade: 3rd

Third grade students got a lesson in economic choices, thanks to the UC Step Store. Each quarter, students earn "Step Bucks" for making good choices such as coming to school on time, maintaining good behavior throughout the day, and working hard on their academic assignments. At the end of each quarter, students add up the "Bucks" they've earned to determine their total for that quarter. Students then get to decide what to do with their earnings. They can spend, donate, or save their Bucks. It's always fun to watch the students make their economic choices!

post_text:
CHECK THIS OUT! Mr. Moulton's 5th-grade class is writing letters to a class in Australia. The purpose of the letter is to understand the differences in the current seasons in both places.

In class, students were discussing the differences in Northern Hemisphere vs Southern Hemisphere. They are hoping to develop some understanding of climate, but they are also asking other questions about the student's personal life to try and get to know them!

What a cool experience for our 5th graders!

Deer Park Community City Schools added 30 new photos.
October 5, 2019 at 9:00 PM ·

Featured Grade: 4th

Third and Fourth graders practiced bus safety this week. They did a great job!

Students continue to work very hard in our new Bridges math curriculum. These mathematicians get to use a variety of math strategies and math tools in a collaborative environment to become better problem solvers. It’s exciting to see their thinking in action.

Mrs. Soellner’s fourth-grade class earned Golden Cat Cards for safe, respectful and responsible behavior. As their reward, they chose to have lunch with the principal. They loved spending time with Mr. Drouhard!

Mrs. Soellner’s class has also been incorporating acts of kindness throughout the day. They start their day with a special morning greeting to each of their classmates. This has been a great way to start the day in a positive way and grow in our Amity friendships!
